MeshBuilder wrongly calculates the number of vertices in MeshPart and the result is:

``` java
meshPart.numVersices != meshPart.mesh.getNumVertices()
```

for Model that contains only one MeshPart - in my case.

com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g3d.utils.MeshBuilder.java near line 175:

``` java
    private void endpart() {
        if (part != null) {
            part.indexOffset = istart;
            part.numVertices = indices.size - istart; // <---
            istart = indices.size;
            part = null;
        }
    }
```

The number of vertices in the mesh part:

``` java
part.numVertices = indices.size - istart;
```

should be (as I guess) calculated with use of the attribute:

``` java
vindex
```

instead of using the indices' offsets, for some meshes (triangle strips etc) one vertex can be pointed by multiple indices, thus num of vertices != num of indices in the mesh part.

